	<dd><a name="comment_750" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Gavin</strong> replies:</em> Right-wing politics are hardly the cause of this. Being able to have a perfectly comfortable lifestyle without having to work is a socialist thing. People who have no choice should be supported. People who just cannot be bothered should not.</p> <p>I think the parties all recognise the problem, but it's very, very difficult to solve - at least without causing a lot of suffering to those who do not deserve it. Ultimately, children are the problem. Society feels it is appropriate to care for the innocent, so all you have to do is have a baby if times are hard and you'll be supported. Of course, life is generally still very tough for poor parents, which is not good - but if you make it too easy then even more people would choose that option. It's really not an easy problem to solve.</p>
